Instructions:

Write a program in a class named Shining that prints the following line of output 1000 times:

All work and no play makes Jack a dull boy.
You should not write a program whose source code is 1000 lines long; use methods to shorten the program. What is the shortest program you can write that will produce the 1000 lines of output, using only the material from Chapter 1 (println, methods, etc.)?



Solution:

public class Shining {


    public static void main(String[] args) {
        shiningLine1000();
    }
    
    
    public static void shiningLine() {
        System.out.println("All work and no play makes Jack a dull boy.");
    }
    
    public static void shiningLine5() {
        shiningLine();
        shiningLine();
        shiningLine();
        shiningLine();
        shiningLine();
    }
    
    public static void shiningLine25() {
        shiningLine5();
        shiningLine5();
        shiningLine5();
        shiningLine5();
        shiningLine5();
    }
    
    public static void shiningLine100() {
        shiningLine25();
        shiningLine25();
        shiningLine25();
        shiningLine25();
    }
    
    public static void shiningLine500() {
        shiningLine100();
        shiningLine100();
        shiningLine100();
        shiningLine100();
        shiningLine100();
    }
    
    public static void shiningLine1000() {
        shiningLine500();
        shiningLine500();
    }

}
